 adjustments are simple others are more difficult.";i:10;s:161:"Assuming the garage door opener housing is in good condition you should see an arrow located around the hole for the down travel and up travel adjustment screws.";i:11;s:141:"This arrow will provide direction on which way to turn the screw to move the door lower for the down position and higher for the up position.";i:12;s:87:"A garage door is considered bound when its difficult or impossible to move up and down.";i:13;s:66:"The following is a guide of how to adjust the tracks to unbind it.";i:14;s:34:"Loosening the Screws on the Track.";i:15;s:100:"Use a screwdriver to loosen the screws that are in the tracks to secure it to the garage door frame.";i:16;s:36:"Adjusting the Position of the Track.";i:17;s:64:"When you are adjusting garage door track you want the door down.";i:18;s:75:"Only loosen one track at a time and do not remove the lag bolts completely.";i:19;s:105:"Loosen the lag bolts that hold the track to the jamb and slide the bracket until the distance is correct.";i:20;s:138:"To adjust your garage doors side-mounted springs first open your door fully and secure it in place with a c-clamp below the bottom roller.";i:21;s:147:"Once your garage door is secured remove the spring hook from the track hanger which will allow you to move the hook and adjust the springs tension.";i:22;s:60:"UP down Garage Door UP down Garage Door UP down Garage Door.";i:23;s:132:"Our Tune Up includes adjustment of the chain tension lubrication and a visual inspection of the rollers hinges bearings and springs.";i:24;s:81:"Dont risk further damage to your home by letting maintenance fall by the wayside.";i:25;s:44:"Let us save you time take care of your door.";i:26;s:69:"If the door stops halfway the up switch probably needs an adjustment.";i:27;s:56:"Measure the distance from the opened door to the ground.";i:28;s:65:"Youll use this measurement when it comes to adjusting the switch.";i:29;s:109:"If you want to see whether theres an issue with the down switch close the garage door and watch it carefully.";i:30;s:69:"If the door stops halfway the up switch probably needs an adjustment.";i:31;s:56:"Measure the distance from the opened door to the ground.";i:32;s:65:"Youll use this measurement when it comes to adjusting the switch.";i:33;s:109:"If you want to see whether theres an issue with the down switch close the garage door and watch it carefully.";i:34;s:133:"If your door doesnt rise at least five feet when it is suppose to be opening hold the bottom of the garage door while it is lowering.";i:35;s:32:"This will adjust the open force.";i:36;s:96:"For a door that doesnt reverse while closing hold the door as it opens to adjust the down force.";i:37;s:23:"Step 1 - Push the Door.";i:38;s:71:"Push the door back to adjust the door and get the center-aligned again.";i:39;s:125:"It is possible that the vertical track down the side has gone out of alignment and shifted due to a slightly loose lag screw.";i:40;s:43:"By pushing the door back into position you.";i:41;s:18:"January 31st 2012.";i:42;s:114:"The travel limit adjustment screws on my Craftsman 12 hp garage door opener are not adjusting the travel distance.";i:43;s:81:"The door hits the floor and reverses up all the way to the Cover Protection Bolt.";i:44;s:80:"Neither the up nor the down travel distance is responding to turning the screws.";i:45;s:82:"Turn the screw marked Close or Down counterclockwise using a flathead screwdriver.";i:46;s:41:"Turn the screw one-half to one full turn.";i:47;s:62:"This may only move the door two or three inches closer to the.";i:48;s:93:"The limit adjustment screw will need to be turned clockwise in order to get it open properly.";i:49;s:97:"If your door is reversing when you go to close it it could be that the sensors are being blocked.";i:50;s:51:"Remove anything blocking the sensors and try again.";i:51;s:75:"If this isnt the problem then youll need to increase the force of the door.";i:52;s:31:"Setting the DownClosed Limit 1.";i:53;s:42:"The door should be in the UpOpen position.";i:54;s:106:"Press and hold the purple or yellow button until the garage door reaches your desired DownClosed position.";i:55;s:105:"When the garage door reaches the DownClosed position you can make adjustments using the black button for.";i:56;s:87:"To test the down limit setting place a 24 on the ground beneath the bottom of the door.";i:57;s:64:"The door should reverse when it comes in contact with the block.";i:58;s:184:"Many home inspectors use this wood block method however Precision Garage Door typically uses a slightly softer item to make the door more sensitive to obstructions and increase safety.";i:59;s:133:"Using a flathead screwdriver turn the down limit switch adjustment screw on the side of the garage door opener clockwise by one turn.";i:60;s:115:"Open and close the garage door adjusting the down limit switch one turn at a time until the door operates normally.";}}